            "icon": "glyphicon glyphicon-text-background",
            "item_title": "Anota\u00e7\u00f5es (20/11/2025, 02:41:10)",
            "item_type": "note",
            "item_note": "<div class=\"zotero-note znv1\"><div data-citation-items=\"%5B%7B%22uris%22%3A%5B%22http%3A%2F%2Fzotero.org%2Fusers%2Flocal%2FZBIgIGVI%2Fitems%2FC2U4P92V%22%5D%2C%22itemData%22%3A%7B%22id%22%3A%22http%3A%2F%2Fzotero.org%2Fusers%2Flocal%2FZBIgIGVI%2Fitems%2FC2U4P92V%22%2C%22type%22%3A%22article-journal%22%2C%22language%22%3A%22en%22%2C%22source%22%3A%22Zotero%22%2C%22title%22%3A%22Digital%20Platforms%20as%20Rule-Makers%3A%20Beyond%20Business%20Models%20to%20Private%20Regulation%22%2C%22author%22%3A%5B%7B%22family%22%3A%22Madhulika%22%2C%22given%22%3A%22Kaul%22%7D%5D%2C%22citation-key%22%3A%22madhulikaDigitalPlatformsRuleMakers%22%7D%7D%5D\" data-schema-version=\"9\"><h1>Anota\u00e7\u00f5es<br/>(20/11/2025, 02:41:10)</h1>\n<p><span class=\"highlight\" data-annotation=\"%7B%22attachmentURI%22%3A%22http%3A%2F%2Fzotero.org%2Fusers%2Flocal%2FZBIgIGVI%2Fitems%2FPGPDJM4A%22%2C%22annotationKey%22%3A%22QK7QBZEW%22%2C%22color%22%3A%22%23fff6cc%22%2C%22pageLabel%22%3A%221%22%2C%22position%22%3A%7B%22pageIndex%22%3A0%2C%22rects%22%3A%5B%5B52.824%2C1032.461%2C738.633%2C1071.491%5D%2C%5B52.824%2C985.008%2C435.806%2C1024.038%5D%2C%5B60.014%2C956.266%2C89.452%2C964.782%5D%2C%5B204.289%2C950.667%2C771.663%2C963.44%5D%2C%5B204.289%2C930.967%2C757.828%2C943.74%5D%2C%5B52.824%2C927.885%2C113.822%2C937.82%5D%2C%5B52.824%2C916.651%2C132.07%2C925.166%5D%2C%5B204.289%2C911.266%2C393.871%2C924.04%5D%2C%5B204.289%2C880.063%2C280.696%2C892.836%5D%2C%5B204.289%2C848.859%2C765.71%2C861.632%5D%2C%5B204.289%2C829.224%2C430.768%2C841.932%5D%2C%5B204.289%2C810.178%2C767.069%2C822.951%5D%2C%5B204.289%2C790.543%2C539.102%2C803.251%5D%2C%5B204.289%2C771.497%2C696.64%2C784.27%5D%2C%5B204.289%2C751.862%2C705.208%2C764.57%5D%5D%7D%2C%22citationItem%22%3A%7B%22uris%22%3A%5B%22http%3A%2F%2Fzotero.org%2Fusers%2Flocal%2FZBIgIGVI%2Fitems%2FC2U4P92V%22%5D%2C%22locator%22%3A%221%22%7D%7D\">\u201cDigital Platforms as Rule-Makers: Beyond Business Models to Private Regulation STRATEGY Published on: DECEMBER 13TH, 2024 Digital platforms function as private regulators in the society. What are the consequences, direct and unintended, of these platforms\u2019 rule-making choices on individuals, firms, regulators, and social movement organizations? Key findings: - Controlling Social Movements: Platforms mediate resource mobilization for social movements, potentially restricting collective action. - Complementor Compliance: Digital platforms like Airbnb enforce rules within their ecosystems but often fail to ensure compliance on external platforms. - Creating Professional Classes: Platforms generate new roles, such as professional complementors, who adapt to platform-specific demands, reinforcing network effects.\u201d</span> <span class=\"citation\" data-citation=\"%7B%22citationItems%22%3A%5B%7B%22uris%22%3A%5B%22http%3A%2F%2Fzotero.org%2Fusers%2Flocal%2FZBIgIGVI%2Fitems%2FC2U4P92V%22%5D%2C%22locator%22%3A%221%22%7D%5D%2C%22properties%22%3A%7B%7D%7D\">(<span class=\"citation-item\">Madhulika, p. 1</span>)</span></p>\n</div></div>",
