            "Abstract Note",
            "The article deals with connected contracts in the strict sense and with networked contracts, both included in the category of connected contracts in the broad sense, with the general objective of pointing out the most common legal implications regarding such contracts. Its specific objectives are (a) to define the contratual coalition and connection; (b) to clarify the hypotheses of the abuse of rights in connected contracts; and (c) to elucidate the role of the Judiciary in cases where there is a violation of objective good faith in the establishment of contractual connections."
